1
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:54,000
Am I poisoned?

2
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:00,540
Take me down the mountain.

3
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,200
If you try to run,

4
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,880
and get a hundred steps away from me,

5
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,280
the poison will surely kill you.

6
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,280
You have a fever.

7
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,560
The dew is heavy at night.

8
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,560
Even if you drill all night,

9
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,280
you won't start a fire.

10
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,040
It's better than freezing to death.

11
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,480
The storybooks say this is how you start a fire.

12
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,680
Why isn't it working?

13
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:20,000
Judging by your clothes,

14
00:03:20,079 --> 00:03:22,400
you're not with those bandits.

15
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:30,720
I'm so handsome and dashing.

16
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,260
Do I look like a bandit?

17
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,840
What is wrong with you?

18
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,800
I saved your life.

19
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,000
I'm your savior.

20
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,100
I even saved you twice.

21
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:51,720
Then why were you at the Prince of Zhenbei's Manor that day?

22
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:56,680
And who was the person wearing the groom's outfit?

23
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,600
I'm a friend of the Heir.

24
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,120
I knew he was getting married,

25
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:06,720
so I went to congratulate him.

26
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:08,440
I wanted to crash the bridal chamber.

27
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:09,680
But...

28
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,250
I just...

29
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,320
saw that corpse.

30
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,690
I don't know anything else.

31
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:18,779
Why are you acting guilty?

32
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:25,400
The smell of blood.

33
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,159
When did I get hurt?

34
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,720
Probably scraped it when crawling through the wood just now.

35
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,320
But why don't I feel anything?

36
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,120
Because I poisoned you.

37
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:48,890
So you've lost your sense of touch.

38
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:53,240
Next, your smell, hearing, taste, and sight...

39
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,760
once all five senses are gone,

40
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:57,120
you will be dead.

41
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,000
Are you serious?

42
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,040
Father,

43
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:07,480
is this the gentle and virtuous daughter-in-law you talked about?

44
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,480
Where is the antidote? Give it to me.

45
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:15,800
Get me down the mountain safely, and I'll cure you.

46
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,560
I was kind enough to save you,

47
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,220
and you actually poisoned me.

48
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,320
If you don't give me the antidote,

49
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,850
I'm leaving you here today.

50
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,120
You win.

51
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,159
I admit defeat today.

52
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,000
Once you give me the antidote,

53
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,400
we'll settle this score.

54
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,480
Let's go.

55
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,320
Hey.

56
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:10,340
You don't know the way.

57
00:06:11,800 --> 00:06:13,800
It's my first time in the mountains.

58
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:16,370
It's normal not to know the way, right?

59
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,640
I need to find my horse.

60
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:25,800
Your horse has returned to the wild.

61
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,730
It's no longer enslaved by humans.

62
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:33,680
Luckily, it didn't fall down with us.

63
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,280
Otherwise, it would be dead.

64
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:41,600
An old horse knows the way back.

65
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:44,500
So that's how it is.

66
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,760
No wonder storybooks say

67
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:49,200
that every hero has their own trusty steed.

68
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:55,000
He doesn't even know this common sense,

69
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,960
yet he doesn't look like a fool.

70
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,600
I walked around just now,

71
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,040
and I can roughly tell the direction.

72
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,440
But it's cloudy today.

73
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:08,920
Without the moon,

74
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,880
the way down might be hard to find.

75
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:16,080
Then keep making the fire.

76
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,250
No need for that.

77
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:25,060
I remember there is a small cabin to the south ahead.

78
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:27,320
We can rest there for a while,

79
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:30,120
and go down the mountain after daybreak tomorrow.

80
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,040
But there are trees everywhere.

81
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,380
Which way is south and which is north?

82
00:07:43,080 --> 00:07:44,280
Look over there.

83
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,920
Take the leaves on the south side for example.

84
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,720
They get more sunlight,

85
00:07:49,159 --> 00:07:51,760
so the branches are lush

86
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,960
and the bark is smoother.

87
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,120
But on the north side,

88
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,240
there's less light,

89
00:07:59,640 --> 00:08:00,600
so the leaves

90
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,720
are sparse

91
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:03,720
and the bark is rougher.

92
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:09,480
You can distinguish south from north using these features.

93
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,740
You actually know about this?

94
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:17,320
I followed my master to travel the world when I was young,

95
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,120
so I learned quite a lot.

96
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,400
I didn't expect Chancellor Ji's daughter

97
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,600
to be even freer than a man like me.

98
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,559
Get on. Otherwise, it'll be dawn soon.

99
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,160
Hold on tight.

100
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,770
If you fall, don't blame me.

101
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:58,880
Found it.

102
00:08:59,400 --> 00:09:01,000
Look, I'm not bad, am I?

103
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,120
Not even a little?

104
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:07,040
She's asleep.

105
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,780
It seems the poison hasn't gone deep yet.

106
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,120
Other girls smell of rouge.

107
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:21,920
But you smell entirely of medicinal herbs.

108
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,320
It doesn't look like nobody lives here.

109
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,840
Jiujiu.

110
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:23,920
Why do you still look like you did as a child?

111
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,240
Jiujiu?

112
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,600
You daughter of the Prime Minister.

113
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,000
You're already engaged,

114
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:45,530
yet you call out another's name in your sleep.

115
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:47,840
Forget it.

116
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,800
Since you're a patient,

117
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,570
I won't hold it against you.

118
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,280
Did you sneak out, too?

119
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,000
Don't tell me you didn't come to find me,

120
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:09,930
but to find that Jiujiu?

121
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,000
Wake up.

122
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,600
Thanks for taking care of me.

123
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,080
I'm just glad you're okay.

124
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,800
If you died, who would I get the antidote from?

125
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,080
This place...

126
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,000
This is...

127
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,520
where Madam Shen Jiujiu lived in seclusion.

128
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,240
Where is the owner of this house?

129
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,300
Have you seen them?

130
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,760
Why are you so nervous?

131
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,820
There was no one here when we arrived.

132
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,840
Drink some water.

133
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,480
Don't worry.

134
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,000
I didn't poison it while you were sleeping.

135
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,380
I know you wouldn't poison me.

136
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:38,480
It's just,

137
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:40,800
you drank from it.

138
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:47,160
Please get me some fresh water.

139
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:48,640
You...

140
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,480
You...

141
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,810
You're disgusted by me?

142
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,160
Men and women should keep their distance.

143
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,280
Keep our distance?

144
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,120
Don't you know

145
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:58,850
that I am your

146
00:12:58,920 --> 00:12:59,640
savior?

147
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,800
Is that you coming back, Savior?

148
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,280
Savior.

149
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:05,120
You are?

150
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:06,680
Who

151
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,480
are you?

152
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:10,320
Watch out.

153
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:45,520
Wu, Zhang, Li, Zheng, Chen, Luo, Deng.

154
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:44,480
Yiyi.

155
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:45,520
Xiao Xiaoxue, Yi, Yi, Nan.

156
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:45,840
Wu, Zhang, Li, Zheng, Chen, Luo, Deng.

157
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,680
Xiao Xiaoxue.

158
00:14:12,680 --> 00:14:12,960
Miao, Lu, Ran.

159
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:13,680
Ma, Miao, Lu, Ran.

160
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:14,280
Ma, Miao, Lu.

161
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,280
Ma, Miao, Lu, Ran.

162
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:20,400
Lyu, Sun, Zhang, Meng.
